STIPULATION FOR DISMISSAL
Pursuant to Fed. R. Civ. P. 41(a)(1)(A)(ii), and in light of the fact that no binding judgment has been entered in this matter consistent with Federal Rule of Civil Procedure 58, Plaintiffs Jane Doe and Susan Roe and Defendants Lloyd J. Austin, III, in his official capacity as Secretary of Defense; the U.S. Department of Defense; the U.S. Defense Health Agency; and the TRICARE Health Plan, hereby stipulate to the dismissal of this action with prejudice and without attorneys’ fees or costs to either party. Dated: December 20, 2024
